# ClaudeCraft OpenClaw secrets (TEMPLATE)
# Copy this to .env.openclaw and fill it in. NEVER commit the real file.
# NEVER paste these values into a chat with Claude — set them directly here.
#
# GOLDEN RULES:
#   1. Use a DEDICATED, throwaway Anthropic API key with a low spend cap —
#      not your main one. Create one at console.anthropic.com. This key now
#      drafts 2 articles + escalation reviews daily (web search included) —
#      double-check the spend cap is still comfortable for that volume.
#   2. Use the SAME restricted Stripe key already used for checkout, but make
#      sure it has "Checkout Sessions: Read" permission added (Write alone
#      isn't enough to pull the sales summary).
#   3. ARTICLES_API_TOKEN must be the EXACT SAME value as the main
#      claudecraft web service's ARTICLES_API_TOKEN env var on Railway —
#      this is how OpenClaw authenticates to publish articles and read the
#      support escalation queue. Without this matching, publishing silently
#      fails with a 401 and nothing ever appears on the live site.
#   4. PUBLIC_BASE_URL should be the live site's real URL (e.g.
#      https://claudecraft.ca) — this is where articles get published to
#      and where escalations get read from.
#   5. Put NOTHING here related to banking, your primary email, or anything
#      beyond these scoped keys.

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=

ARTICLES_API_TOKEN=

PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://claudecraft.ca
